    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1366">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/206.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to inform your
                    excellency that my Government, to which I forwarded in due time the contents of
                    your excellency’s note of February 19th last<note n="115" xml:id="d1366fn115"
                        >Not printed.</note> relative to the murder of the Spanish subjects Gonzalez
                    brothers at Chihuahua, instructs me to express its thanks for the attitude of
                    the United States in the case and, at the same time, to say to your excellency
                    that it cherishes the hope that your excellency will insist by all means at your
                    disposal that a thorough investigation of the facts be made by the
                    Constitutionalist authorities.</p>
                <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
